          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Common Mistakes"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "table",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Mistake"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Problem"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableHeader",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Fix"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Using json_object mode without a schema description in the prompt"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Model may output any valid JSON with unpredictable field names"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Always include schema description in system prompt when using JSON mode"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Not setting additionalProperties: false in strict mode"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "API returns an error — strict mode requires this constraint"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Add \"additionalProperties\": false to every object in the schema"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Making fields optional in strict mode"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Strict mode requires all properties to be listed under required"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Use nullable types ([\"string\", \"null\"]) for optional fields instead of omitting from required"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "tableRow",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Trusting format constraints (date-time, email)"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Format hints are not enforced; model may produce invalid dates"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              },
              {
                "type": "tableCell",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "paragraph",
                    "content": [
                      {
                        "type": "text",
                        "text": "Validate format-constrained fields with Python's datetime.fromisoformat() or similar"
                      }
                    ]
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "text",
            "text": "Best Practices"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "bulletList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Use Pydantic models as the single source of truth for schema definition. The openai.beta.chat.completions.parse() method derives the JSON Schema automatically from a Pydantic model, eliminating the risk of discrepancies between the schema and the application's data model."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "For Anthropic, the tool-use pattern is more robust than the assistant-prefill pattern because tool call arguments are validated server-side. Reserve assistant prefill for simple structures where full schema enforcement is not critical."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Keep schemas as flat and simple as possible. Deeply nested schemas with many optional fields are harder for the model to fill correctly and harder to validate. Prefer wide-and-shallow over narrow-and-deep."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Include field descriptions in the schema (the description property). The model uses these to understand what to extract. A field named city with description \"City of residence, or null if not mentioned\" produces better results than an undocumented field."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "listItem",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "paragraph",
                "content": [
                  {
                    "type": "text",
                    "text": "Set temperature=0 for extraction and classification tasks. Structured output constrains the shape but not the content — a higher temperature still introduces variability in values like confidence scores or chosen categories."
                  }
                ]
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "blockquote",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "paragraph",
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "text",
                "text": "Structured output APIs are the right tool whenever an application needs to consume the model's output as data rather than text. The hierarchy of reliability is: prompt-only < JSON mode < JSON Schema (strict=true). For OpenAI, use Pydantic with parse() for the most ergonomic and type-safe approach. For Anthropic, force a tool call with the desired input schema to get server-validated structured output. In either case, include field descriptions in the schema to guide the model on what to extract, and test with inputs where fields are absent or ambiguous to verify the model's null/default handling."
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  }
}
